# HEYDAY workflow

## Requirements

- Everything the user states in a task is **acceptance criteria**, not nice-to-have
- Mockups/screenshots are the **acceptance test**, not inspiration
- If ambiguous, ask once — do not silently drop scope

## Agent prompts (when user asks for one)

Use a copy-paste block with:

GOAL · REFERENCE · LAYOUT (numbered) · COMPONENTS (path → duty) · DATA (fields + formulas) · INTERACTIONS · DO NOT · ACCEPTANCE [ ] · VERIFY

Use **behavior-level bullets**, not vague labels. Example quality:

```
Weekly quota cards (PlatformQuotasRow.jsx):
- 5 cards: Marketing Status | Instagram | LinkedIn | TikTok | Newsletters
- Fraction count/target, progress bar, footer NEXT: {title or —}
- GOAL MET if count >= target; ATTENTION REQUIRED if count === 0 and weekday >= Wed
- Target: first integer in platform_goals.frequency, else 2
```

End with: `npm run build must pass. No commit unless asked.`

## UI pages

- Marketing calendar (done): weekly quota cards + hero calendar grid — see `client/src/components/marketing/`
- `DashboardLayout compactHeader` for full-bleed pages (no duplicate TopNav title/search)
- Full width main content — no `max-w` caps that leave dead right margin

## Session handoff

Prefer one slice per agent session (single feature/fix). User may start new chats with this rules folder loaded — do not assume prior chat memory.
